> I'd like to know what is maximum number of ethernet cards that linux
> support and what makes that limit? I'd like to know that for 2.2 and
> 2.4, if it is different.
Approximately 2 per Kb of memory in the machine but I wouldnt suggest using
that many.
Seriously you will run out of slots, memory and cpu power before cards.
